Kaizer Chiefs of South Africa goalkeeper, Daniel Akpeyi says he felt honoured to be counted among the 28 players representing Nigeria at the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations holding in Cameroon. Akpeyi who was the first choice at the last AFCON in Egypt 2019 called it a privilege to be selected again for another one. “Nigeria is a big country and if you happen to be included even in the 50 man list you should be grateful it is a great privilege,” Akpeyi said .”For me, it is a great privilege to be on the 28-man list.” Meanwhile, goaltender John Noble is certain Nigeria has the quality to qualify from Group D and go ahead to win their fourth Africa Cup of Nations title in Cameroon.   BetKing to fly five fans to watch AFCON finals     Covid chaos stop Senegal flight to Cameroon     Salah issues AFCON battle cry   Noble who expressed his delight at his selection for the 2021 AFCON stressed that Egypt, Sudan, and Guinea Bissau would not hinder the Eagles’ second round qualification. - Advertisement - “For me, I am very happy because it is the dream of every player to represent his country. When I saw my name on the list I was so happy and I returned all the glories to God,” Noble told journalists. “I believe in the quality of players the Super Eagles have. We are doing well for our different clubs. I do believe we will qualify from the group stage. “I know the inability to train as a team for a long period of time may affect us in Cameroon but we are professionals. We are going there to make the country proud and to put in our best. Everyone is willing to work and with the cooperation in the team, I quite believe that we are going to bring the country to Nigeria,” the Enyimba goalkeeper said.